svg.text: Image showing deprivation profiles of General Electoral Districts in New Zealand. To create the shapes, data zones in New Zealand
were ranked using the New Zealand Index of Multiple Deprivation measure, and were divided into twenty buckets
(vigintiles). The distribution of data zones in each general electoral district was plotted, with more deprived data zones at the
bottom of the plots, and less deprived data zones at the top. To interpret the shapes - a larger bottom indicates
more deprived data zones in the area, while a larger top indicates fewer deprived data zones.
Data: New Zealand Index of Multiple Deprivation | https://www.fmhs.auckland.ac.nz/en/soph/about/
Visualisation created in R Studio and Adobe Illustrator by Jamie Whyte and Julian Tait of Open Data Manchester
GEDs are sorted according to the average rank of data zones in each district.
